&nbsp;
Italy then freed itself "from the occupying Nazi, from a terrible war, but also from a ruthless dictatorship that, along the span of twenty years, had suffocated political and civil rights, trampled fundamental freedoms, persecuted Jews and minorities, educated young people to the sacrilege religion of violence and abuse. The entry into the war, alongside Hitler, was the direct and inevitable consequence of this climate of fanatical exaltation ".
